                        <msContents>
                            <summary>Early 18th century copy of a Turkish version of <title
                                    xml:lang="ota-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21082">Naṣīḥat al-Mulūk
                                </title> by
                                    <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard" role="ant"
                                        key="person_31996761" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/31996761"
                                        >Ghazzālī, 1058-1111</persName>. The translator is unnamed. An introduction
                                (folios <locus from="1b" to="5a">1b-5a</locus>) contains paragraphs
                                in praise of <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard"
                                    role="dte" key="person_31996761"
                                    ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/31996761">Sultan Selim II</persName>
                                and Grand Vizier <persName key="person_f6434" role="pat">Soḳollu Mehmed Paşa,
                                    1505-1579</persName>, explaining that it was commissioned by the
                                latter when he was Governor of Aleppo (between 1551 and
                                1553).</summary>
                            <msItem xml:id="Turkish_MS_73-part1-item1">
                                <locus from="1b" to="62b">1b-62b</locus>
                                <author>
                                    <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard" role="ant"
                                        key="person_31996761" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/31996761"
                                        >Ghazzālī, 1058-1111</persName>
                                </author>
                                <editor role="trl">Anonymous</editor>
                                <title xml:lang="ota-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21195">Ādābu al-Mulūk </title>
                                <title xml:lang="ota" key="work_21195">اداب الملوك </title>
                                <title xml:lang="ota-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21195" type="alt">Naṣīḥat
                                    al-Mulūk</title>
                                <title xml:lang="ota" type="alt" key="work_21195">نصيحة الملوك </title>
                                <incipit xml:lang="ota">حمد نامحدود و ثنا نا معدود حضرت حليم خلاق و
                                    حكيم على الاطلاق جلت قدرته علت كلمته يه كه<locus from="1b">
                                        (folio 1b) </locus></incipit>
                                <explicit xml:lang="ota">النسان كل بلاد ياتى منهن و الوفا لا ياتى
                                    مدد الازمان<locus from="62b"> (folio 62b) </locus></explicit>
                                <textLang mainLang="ota">Ottoman Turkish</textLang>
                            </msItem>
                        </msContents>
