                            <summary>A mid 18th century copy of the Vefayāt, a biographical
                                dictionary which includes entries for notable people buried in
                                Bursa. </summary>
                            <msItem xml:id="Turkish_MS_73-part2-item1">
                                <locus from="65b" to="203a">65b-203a</locus>
                                <author key="person_55371823" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/55371823">
                                    <persName type="standard">Baldırzade Selı̂sı̂ Şeyh Mehmed, d.
                                        1650 </persName>
                                </author>
                                <title xml:lang="ota-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21324"
                                    >Vefayāt-nāme</title>
                                <title xml:lang="ota">وفياتنامه</title>
                                <title xml:lang="ota-Latn-x-lc" type="alt">Ravzatu'l-evliya</title>
                                <title xml:lang="ota" type="alt">روضة الاولياء</title>
                                <incipit xml:lang="ota">حمد نا محدود و ثنا غير معدود اول واجب و مفيض
                                    اكخير و الجود<locus from="65b"> (65b) </locus></incipit>
                                <explicit xml:lang="ota">الحمد للة تعالى مناصب و مراتبدن بالكليه
                                    فراغ اولنمشدر بو محلده تمام اولدقده الحمد للة ولى الانعام الى
                                    قيام الساعة و ساعة قيام <locus from="203a"> (203a)
                                    </locus></explicit>
                                <textLang mainLang="ota">Ottoman Turkish</textLang>
                                <note>Begins with Shams ad-Dīn Muhammad, known as Amīr Sultān (d
                                    1439) on folio <locus from="66a" to="66a">66a</locus> and ends
                                    with Ebu Ishak on folio <locus from="199a" to="199a"
                                        >199a</locus>. Concludes with an appendix including the
                                    author's own biography. There is a fragment of Arabic prose on
                                    folio <locus from="64b" to="64b">64b</locus>.</note>
                                <listBibl>
                                    <bibl><ref target="http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/609341754"
                                            >Baldırzade, Selı̂sı̂ S. M, Mefail Hızlı and Murat
                                            Yurtsever (ed), Ravza-i Evliya, Çekirge, Bursa [Turkey:
                                            Arasta Yayınları], 2000.</ref></bibl>
                                </listBibl>
                            </msItem>
